in%20the%20second%20district%2C%20but%20doesn't%20give%20them%20the%20majority.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20high%20court%20had%20said%20the%20existing%20map%20violated%20the%20Voting%20Rights%20Act%20by%20diluting%20Black%20voters'%20power.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlabama%20is%20ignoring%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20that%20demanded%20the%20state%20redraw%20its%20district%20maps%20to%20include%20a%20second%20Black-majority%20district%20in%20the%20state%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fregulation%2Fcourt-battles%2F4102476-proposed-alabama-district-map-rejects-supreme-court-mandated-second-black-majority-district%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Hill%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkavanaugh-racial-gerrymander-map-reversal-decision-2023-6%5C%22%3E5-4%20June%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20sided%20with%20a%20group%20of%20voters%20that%20claimed%20the%20state's%20current%20district%20map%20violates%20the%20Voting%20Rights%20Act%20because%20it%20includes%20just%20one%20Black-majority%20district%20out%20of%20seven%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20state%20that%20has%20a%20population%20of%20Black%20voters%20of%2027%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20came%20as%20a%20surprise%20as%20Chief%20Justice%20John%20Roberts%20and%20conservative%20Brett%20Kavanaugh%20sided%20with%20the%20court's%20three%20liberal%20justices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Hill%2C%20the%20team%20of%20Republicans%20tasked%20with%20redrawing%20Alabama's%20district%20map%20aren't%20listening%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20ruling.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20lawmakers%20on%20Monday%20proposed%20their%20new%20version%20of%20the%20districting%20map%20which%20increased%20the%20number%20of%20Black%20voters%20in%20the%20second%20district%20from%2030%25%20to%20nearly%2042.5%25%2C%20The%20Hill%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20June%20ruling%2C%20though%2C%20that%20second%20district%20would%20have%20to%20include%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20Black%20voters%2C%20or%20at%20least%20be%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bperform%26quot%3B%20for%20Black%20voters%2C%20giving%20a%20candidate%20supported%20by%20Black%20voters%20in%20the%20state%20a%20real%20chance%20to%20win%2C%20Mark%20Gaber%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20redistricting%20at%20Campaign%20Legal%20Center%2C%20explained%20to%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20it's%20not%20about%20the%20percentage%20of%20Black%20voters%20in%20the%20district%2C%20Gaber%20said.%20It's%20more%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20this%20proposed%20district%20is%20in%20rural%20Alabama%2C%20where%20voting%20is%20hyper-polarized%2C%20so%20Black%20voters%20would%20need%20a%20majority%20to%20ever%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20elect%20a%20candidate%20they%20support.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20if%20a%20second%20district%20were%20drawn%20near%20a%20big%20city%2C%20like%20Birmingham%20%E2%80%94%20where%20voting%20is%20still%20polarized%20but%20not%20as%20much%20%E2%80%94%20the%20district%20might%20not%20need%20to%20account%20for%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20Black%20voters%20because%20there%20is%20more%20of%20an%20opportunity%20there%2C%20Gaber%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20key%20thing%20is%20like%20functionally%2C%20looking%20to%20see%20election%20results%20and%20whether%20or%20not%20in%20the%20district%20that's%20drawn%20the%20past%20candidates%20favored%20by%20Black%20voters%20actually%20prevailed%20in%20the%20district%20as%20a%20function%2C%26quot%3B%20Gaber%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20reality%20in%20Alabama%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20the%20voting%20is%20so%20racially%20polarized%20that%20the%20white%20voters%20have%20such%20low%20support%20for%20candidates%20supported%20by%20Black%20voters%20that%20as%20a%20functional%20matter%2C%20it%20does%20need%20to%20be%2C%20as%20the%20district%20court%20said%2C%20either%20a%20majority%20or%20close%20to%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20was%20approved%20by%20the%20Permanent%20Legislative%20Committee%20in%20a%2014-6%20vote%20across%20party%20lines%2C%20The%20Hill%20reported.%20Gaber%20said%20the%20proposed%20map%20is%20%26quot%3Bviolating%20section%20two%20of%20the%20Voting%20Rights%20Act.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlabama's%20Republican%20House%20Speaker%20Pro%20Tempore%20Chris%20Pringle%20%E2%80%94%20who%20also%20serves%20as%20the%20co-chairman%20of%20Alabama's%20redistricting%20committee%20%E2%80%94%20stood%20by%20this%20committee's%20proposal%20when%20it%20was%20introduced%20in%20a%20special%20session%20Monday%2C%20saying%20it%20gave%20Black%20voters%20a%20bigger%20voice%20and%20that%20was%20enough.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20took%20in%20consideration%20what%20the%20court%20asked%20us%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Pringle%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F07%2F17%2Falabama-republicans-reject-second-majority-black-house-district-00106675%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Politico%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Redistricting%20Foundation%2C%20a%20Democratic-Party-aligned%20nonprofit%20that%20was%20among%20those%20opposing%20the%20Alabama%20maps%2C%20vowed%20to%20fight%20the%20new%20maps%20if%20they%20are%20approved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlabama%20Republicans%20are%20intentionally%20drawing%20political%20retention%20maps%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20Black%20Alabamians%E2%80%94in%20defiance%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20Alabama%20district%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20Executive%20Director%20Marina%20Jenkins%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fredistrictingfoundation.org%2Fnews%2Fnrf-responds-to-alabama-republicans-passing-gerrymandered-maps-in-committee%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20continuation%20of%20the%20state's%20long%2C%20sordid%20history%20of%20disenfranchising%20Black%20voters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGaber%20said%20there%20