tive%20Bills%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20environment.%20Our%20prime%20minister%20has%20said%20on%20record%20that%20he%20is%20interested%20in%20protecting%20our%20biodiversity%20and%20forests%2C%20but%20his%20very%20own%20people%20are%20set%20to%20destroy%20the%20forests%20by%20passing%20this%20Amendment%20Bill%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeelam%20Ahluwalia%2C%20founder%20member%20and%20trustee%20of%20the%20Aravalli%20Bachao%20Citizens%20Movement%2C%20said%20that%20the%20forests%2C%20which%20are%20protected%20and%20managed%20by%20local%20communities%2C%20but%20not%20notified%20as%20forests%2C%20will%20be%20decimated%20if%20the%20Bill%20is%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20estimated%20that%20around%2039%2C063%20hectares%20of%20forests%20are%20under%20the%20sacred%20groves%20across%20India%20protected%20and%20managed%20as%20forests%20by%20local%20communities%20even%20though%20they%20are%20not%20currently%20notified%20as%20forests.%20The%20Forest%20Conservation%20Amendment%20Bill%20will%20decimate%20such%20lands%20across%20the%20690%20kilometre%20Aravalli%20range%20spread%20over%20four%20states%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%20Also%2C%20hugely%20at%20risk%20are%2050%2C000%20acres%20of%20Haryana%20Aravallis%20since%20these%20forests%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20notified%20as%20%E2%80%98deemed%20forests%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19201247%2Fimage-1147.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22932%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19201247%2Fimage-1147.png%20932w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19201247%2Fimage-1147-300x151.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664019%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22470%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EProtest%20against%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Amendment%20Bill%20in%20Karjat%2C%20Maharashtra.%20Photo%3A%20By%20special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20courts%20and%20reports%20keep%20pointing%20out%20the%20value%20of%20our%20forests%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20fact%20that%20we%20are%20still%20too%20far%20from%20knowing%20exactly%20how%20much%20these%20ecosystems%20serve%20us.%20Still%2C%20the%20government%20goes%20on%20treating%20our%20forests%20as%20dispensable.%20Be%20it%20the%20Aravallis%2C%20the%20mangroves%20all%20along%20our%20coast%2C%20Western%20and%20Eastern%20Ghats%2C%20biodiversity%20hotspots%20of%20the%20North-East%2C%20our%20rich%20Central%20Indian%20forests%20%E2%80%93%20a%20great%20part%20of%20these%20could%20no%20longer%20be%20considered%20%E2%80%98forest%E2%80%99%20and%20can%20potentially%20be%20sold%2C%20diverted%2C%20cleared%2C%20exploited%20without%20any%20regulatory%20oversight%2C%20if%20the%20new%20amendment%20Bill%20is%20passed%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yash%20Marwah%2C%20co-creator%20of%20Let%20India%20Breathe%2C%20a%20volunteer-run%20environment%20collective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20proposed%20amendments%20severely%20compromise%20the%20constitutional%20mandate%20of%20the%20State%20(Article%2048A)%20to%20safeguard%20forests%2C%20Article%2051A%20(g)%2C%20which%20places%20a%20duty%20on%20the%20citizens%20of%20India%20to%20protect%20and%20improve%20the%20natural%20environment%2C%20and%20jeopardises%20access%20to%20information%2C%20public%20participation%20and%20access%20to%20justice%2C%20which%20are%20essential%20components%20of%20the%20Rio%20Declaration%201992%20and%20fundamental%20rights%20guaranteed%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20250px)%2085vw%2C%20250px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3