ublished%22%3A1689771928000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FD3B8%2Fproduction%2F_130400245_33a00f591958be8a39126852589f7c10fa1f7014.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66219602%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20man%20who%20won%20the%20general%20election%20is%20suspended%20as%20an%20MP%20and%20blocked%20from%20becoming%20prime%20minister.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A583%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66219602%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66219602.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66219602.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Karnataka%20HC%20Stays%20FIR%20Against%20Amit%20Malviya%20for%20Tweet%20About%20Rahul%20Gandhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F29111950%2FTwitter-malviyaamit.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20July%2019%2C%20stayed%20the%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20registered%20against%20BJP%20IT%20cell%20chief%20Amit%20Malviya%20for%20a%20tweet%20on%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20via%20an%20interim%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20registered%20against%20Malviya%20under%20various%20sections%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%2C%20including%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20two%20groups%20and%20criminal%20conspiracy.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fhigh-court%2Fkarnataka-high-court%2Fkarnataka-high-court-stays-investigation-bjp-it-cell-amit-malviya-tweet-rahul-gandhi-congress-leader-233107%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%C2%A0single-judge%20bench%20of%20Justice%20M.%20Nagaprasanna%20observed%20that%20the%20tweet%20in%20question%20was%20against%20an%20individual%20and%20therefore%20cannot%20be%20regarded%20as%20against%20a%20group%2C%20class%20or%20as%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20groups%20or%20classes%20to%20attract%20punishment%20under%20Section%20153A%20of%20the%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tweet%20for%20which%20the%20case%20against%20Malviya%20was%20registered%20had%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Famitmalviya%2Fstatus%2F1669903353336451072%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3Eanimated%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20showed%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20as%20part%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbreak%20India%E2%80%9D%20and.%20The%20FIR%20was%20filed%20based%20on%20a%20complaint%20filed%20by%20Congress%20leaders%20Priyank%20Kharge%20and%20Ramesh%20Babu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20stated%20that%20Malviya%E2%80%99s%20actions%20were%20intended%20to%20%E2%80%9Cincite%20animosity%20and%20hatred%20within%20society%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20MP%20Tejasvi%20Surya%2C%20who%20was%20appearing%20for%20Malviya%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20FIR%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpolitically%20motivated%E2%80%9D%20and%20raised%20the%20possibility%20of%20imminent%20arrest.%20He%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20tweet%20could%20not%20be%20described%20as%20promoting%20enmity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20tweet%20that%20is%20alleged%20or%20which%20has%20become%20the%20fulcrum%20of%20the%20present%20allegation%20is%20against%20an%20individual.%20If%20the%20tweet%20is%20against%20an%20individual%2C%20how%20it%20has%20created%20disharmony%20or%20enmity%20between%20different%20groups%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20religion%2C%20race%2C%20place%20of%20birth%20or%20residence%20is%20not%20divulged%20in%20the%20complaint.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20complaint%20though%20narrates%20that%20it%20amounts%20to%20certain%20extremism%20of%20certain%20religion%20that%20is%20not%20the%20intention%20of%20the%20tweet.%20The%20contention%20is%20that%20it%20is%20against%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress.%20What%20enmity%20the%20tweet%20has%20promoted%20between%20different%20groups%20is%20not%20divulged%20in%20the%20complaint.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20referred%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-quashes-fir-against-journalist-patricia-mukhim-for-facebook-post%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPatricia%20Mukhim%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20interpreted%20the%20scope%20of%20Section%20153A%20IPC.%20It%20said%20allowing%20further%20investigation%20against%20Malviya%2C%20if%20permitted%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20become%20an%20abuse%20of%20process%20of%20law%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20stayed%20the%20investigation%20until%20the%20next%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689771820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F29111950%2FTwitter-malviyaamit.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkarnataka-hc-stay-fir-amit-malviya%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20observed%20that%20the%20tweet%20was%20about%20an%20individual%20and%20cannot%20be%20regarded%20as%20against%20a%20group%2C%20class%20or%20as%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20groups%20or%20classes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkarnataka-hc-stay-fir-amit-malviya%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Is%20a%20film%20on%20Raj%20Kundra%20on%20the%20cards%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689770821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101952785%2Cimgsize-36582.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fis-a-film-on-shilpa-shettys-husband-raj-kundra-on-the-cards-heres-what-we-know-%2Farticleshow%2F101952785