ture%2Farticleshow%2F101951675.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fhome%2Fenvironment%2Fcanadian-wildfires-hit-indigenous-communities-hard-threatening-their-land-and-culture%2Famp_articleshow%2F101951675.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fhome%2Fenvironment%2Fcanadian-wildfires-hit-indigenous-communities-hard-threatening-their-land-and-culture%2Famp_articleshow%2F101951675.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Claiming%20India%20Saw%20'1%2C000%20Years%20of%20Foreign%20Rule'%20Trivialises%20British%20Colonial%20Exploitation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19152924%2Fdelhi-durbar-1911-16609.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20notion%20that%20India%20endured%20several%20centuries%20of%20%E2%80%98foreign%E2%80%99%20rule%20during%20the%20medieval%20period%20was%20firmly%20planted%20by%20colonial%20administrators%20and%20ideologues%20in%20the%20early%20decades%20of%20the%2019th%20century.%20Thus%2C%20Lord%20Ellenborough%20(governor-general%2C%201842-44)%20proclaimed%20in%201842%20that%20by%20transporting%20in%20that%20year%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98Gates%20of%20Somnath%E2%80%99%20from%20Afghanistan%20to%20the%20East%20India%20Company%E2%80%99s%20territories%2C%20%E2%80%98the%20insult%20of%20eight%20hundred%20years%E2%80%99%20had%20been%20%E2%80%98avenged%E2%80%99%20by%20British%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEllenborough%20was%20a%20prominent%20Tory%20politician%20who%20presided%20over%20the%20Board%20of%20Control%2C%20the%20body%20which%20monitored%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20administration%2C%20several%20times%20between%20the%201820s%20and%201858%20(he%20was%20president%20of%20the%20board%20when%20the%20bill%20for%20divesting%20the%20Company%20of%20its%20authority%20to%20govern%20the%20Indian%20empire%20was%20being%20drafted%20in%201858).%20Ellenborough%20had%20put%20together%20an%20armed%20force%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Army%20of%20Retribution%E2%80%99%2C%20for%20marching%20through%20parts%20of%20Afghanistan%20in%20order%20to%20salvage%20imperial%20prestige%20following%20the%20crushing%20defeat%20inflicted%20on%20British%20forces%20in%20the%20First%20Afghan%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20against%20this%20backdrop%20that%20he%20issued%20the%20%E2%80%98eight%20hundred%20years%E2%80%99%20statement%20which%20sought%20to%20portray%20the%20British%20as%20saviours%20of%20Indian%20subjects%20of%20the%20empire!%20Already%20then%20by%20this%20time%20the%20medieval%20period%20had%20come%20to%20be%20equated%20in%20colonial%20writings%20with%20%E2%80%98Muslim%20period%E2%80%99.%20This%20in%20turn%20was%20portrayed%20as%20a%20period%20of%20%E2%80%98foreign%E2%80%99%20rule%2C%20a%20view%20recently%20echoed%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20in%20a%20speech%20in%20the%20US%2C%20which%20referred%20to%20India%20having%20been%20under%20%E2%80%98a%20thousand%20years%20of%20foreign%20rule%20in%20one%20form%20or%20another%E2%80%99.%20The%20British%20of%20course%20subtracted%20the%20period%20of%20colonial%20subjugation%20from%20their%20figure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20conventional%20understanding%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20medieval%20past%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20and%20is%20succinctly%20summed%20up%20in%20a%20widely-read%20work%20published%20at%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%2C%20Stanley%20Lane-poole%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EMediaeval%20India%20Under%20Mohammedan%20Rule%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1903).%20It%20might%20be%20worthwhile%20to%20quote%20the%20opening%20sentences%20of%20the%20Preface%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98The%20Mediaeval%20Period%20of%20Indian%20history%2C%20though%20it%20does%20not%20exactly%20correspond%20with%20the%20Middle%20Age%20of%20Europe%2C%20is%20not%20less%20clearly%20defined.%20It%20begins%20when%20the%20immemorial%20systems%2C%20rule%2C%20and%20customs%20of%20Ancient%20India%20were%20invaded%2C%20subdued%2C%20and%20modified%20by%20a%20succession%20of%20foreign%20conquerors%20who%20imposed%20a%20new%20rule%20%E2%80%A6%20These%20conquerors%20were%20Muslims%2C%20and%20with%20the%20arrival%20of%20the%20Turks%20%E2%80%A6%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20eleventh%20century%2C%20India%20entered%20upon%20her%20Middle%20Age.%20From%20that%20epoch%20for%20nearly%20eight%20hundred%20years%20her%20history%20is%20grouped%20round%20the%20Mohammedan%20rulers%20%E2%80%A6%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeaving%20aside%20the%20evident%20factual%20inaccuracy%20in%20the%20last%20sentence%20of%20the%20above%20quotation%20(mention%20may%20be%20made%20of%2C%20among%20others%2C%20Cholas%2C%20Gajapatis%2C%20Ahoms%2C%20Kakatiyas%3B%20rulers%20of%20Vijayanagara%2C%20Mewar%2C%20Travancore%3B%20and%20the%20Marathas%20from%20the%20late%2017th%20century%20onwards%20%E2%80%93%20none%20of%20whom%20fit%20into%20Lane-poole%E2%80%99s%20generalisation)%2C%20one%20wonders%20whether%20it%20is%20historically%20meaningful%20to%20disregard%20the%20process%20of%20naturalisation.%20It%20is%20ironical%20that%20careers%20of%20contemporary%20western%20elites%20of%20Indian%20descent%20who%20are%20in%20positions%20of%20political%20power%2C%20Nikki%20Haley%2C%20Bobby%20Jindal%20or%20Rishi%20Sunak%20for%20example%2C%20are%20looked%20upon%20as%20migrant%20success%20stories%20which%20are%20worth%20admiring%2C%20whereas%20they%20are%20second%20or%20third%20generation%20settlers.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%20a%20fourth%20generation%20settler%20such%20as%20the%20Jahangir%2C%20born%20and%20brought%20up%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Agra%20risks%20being%20regarded%20as%20an%20%E2%80%98outsider%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Sylhet%20Referendum%20Anniversary%3A%20A%20Time%20to%20Remember%20Partition%20Wasn't%20Only%20About%20a%20Hindu-Muslim%20Binary%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fsylhet-referendum-is-a-reminder-that-partition-wasnt-only-about-a-hindu-muslim-binary%5C%22%3ESylhet%20Referendum%20Anniversary%3A%20A%20Time%20to%20Remember%20Partition%20Wasn%E2%80%99t%20Only%20About%20a%20Hindu-Muslim%20Binary%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20early%2019th%20century%2C%20colonial%20historiography%20divided%20pre-British%20Indian%20history%20into%20periods%20labelled%20in%20terms%20of%20religious%20identity%3A%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim.%20The%20entire%20period%20prior%20to%20circa%201000%20CE%2C%20was%20labelled%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20Period%E2%80%99%20of%20Indian%20history.%20The%20period%20from%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%2011th%20century%20came%20to%20be%20regarded%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Muslim%20Period%E2%80%99%20of%20Indian%20history%2C%20lasting%20till%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%2018th%20century.%20This%20period%20was%20further%20subdivided%20into%20the%20era%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Sultanate%20(1206-1526)%2C%20which%20was%20followed%20by%20the%20Mughal%20era.%20The%20Mughal%20empire%20began%20to%20disintegrate%20after%20the%20death%20of%20Aurangzeb%20(1707).%20The%20conquest%20of%20Bengal%20by%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20was%20regarded%20as%20marking%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20British%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20periodisation%20has%20been%20attributed%20to%20James%20Mill%2C%20whose%20%3Cem%3EHistory%20of%20British%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20in%201817%20remained%20one%20of%20the%20most%20influential%20colonial%20texts%20on%20the%20subject%20throughout%20the%2019th%20century.%20While%20the%20roots%20of%20the%20periodisation%20scheme%20may%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20Mill%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20Mill%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EHistory%3C%2Fem%3E%20would%20show%20that%20he%20does%20not%20actually%20refer%20to%20%E2%80%98Hindu%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Muslim%E2%80%99%20periods%20of%20Indian%20history.%20For%20Mill%2C%20non-European%20societies%20had%20no%20real%20history.%20According%20to%20this%20understanding%2C%20Indian%20society%20had%20been%20changeless%20before%20the%20British%20rule%20was%20introduced.%20Since%20India%2C%20unlike%20Europe%2C%20had%20no%20history%2C%20it%20could%20not%20therefore%20have%20had%20any%20historical%20epochs.%20The%20past%20could%20not%20be%20conceived%20in%20terms%20historical%20periods%2C%20with%20discontinuities%20indicating%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20short%20portion%20of%20the%20first%20volume%20of%20Mill%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20dealing%20with%20%E2%80%98The%20Mahomedans%E2%80%99%2C%20sketches%20the%20political%20history%20of%20north%20India%2C%20from%20Mahmud%E2%80%99s%20forays%20into%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20to%20the%20accession%20of%20Shah%20Alam%20II%20in%201759.%20It%20begins%20with%20the%20assertion%20that%2C%20%E2%80%98At%20the%20time%20when%20the%20nations%20of%20Europe%20opened%20their%20communication%20with%20India%2C%20by%20the%20Cape%20of%20Good%20Hope%20%5Bc.1498%5D%2C%20the%20people%20%E2%80%A6%20for%20a%20number%20of%20ages%20been%20subject%20to%20a%20race%20of%20foreigners%E2%80%99.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20Vasco%20da%20Gama%E2%80%99s%20voyage%2C%20%E2%80%98the%20political%20state%20of%20India%20%E2%80%A6%20consisted%20of%20a%20Mahomedan%20government%2C%20supported%20by%20a%20Mahomedan%20force%2C%20over%20a%20Hindu%20population%E2%80%99.%20This%20was%20a%20key%20formulation%20picked%20up%20by%20some%20of%20the%20Indian%20historians%20writing%20in%20the%20early%20twentieth%20century.%20These%20historians%20sought%20to%20contest%20the%20colonial%20construction%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20past%20by%20postulating%20that%20India%20had%20a%20glorious%20ancient%20civilisation%20which%20was%20disrupted%20when%20India%20came%20under%20Muslim%20rulers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20periodisation%20of%20the%20history%20of%20pre-British%20India%2C%20by%20dividing%20this%20history%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98Hindu%E2%80%99%20period%20and%20a%20%E2%80%98Muslim%E2%80%99%20period%E2%80%99%2C%20had%20become%20well-entrenched%20by%20the%20middle%20of%20the%2019th%20century.%20It%20needs%20to%20be%20underlined%20that%20the%20historiography%20on%20India%20was%20almost%20the%20exclusive%20preserve%20of%20colonial%20bureaucrats%20dabbling%20in%20history%20till%20the%201880s.%20Therefore%20colonial%20narratives%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20past%20remained%20unchallenged%20for%20almost%20three-quarters%20of%20a%20century%20and%20had%20an%20enormous%20impact%20on%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20this%20past%20was%20imagined.%20What%20is%20more%2C%20colonial%20historiography%20provided%20many%20of%20the%20building%20blocks%20for%20early%20nationalist%20historians%2C%20and%20subsequently%20for%20communal%20political%20assertions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMill%E2%80%99s%20book%20had%20no%20serious%20competitor%20for%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20century.%20As%20a%20general%20modern%20history%20of%20India%2C%20purporting%20to%20be%20a%20history%20of%20the%20entire%20subcontinent%2C%20it%20was%20the%20only%20book%20of%20its%20kind%20till%20the%20publication%20of%20a%20book%20which%20focused%20on%20the%20pre-British%20past%20of%20the%20subcontinent.%20It%20was%20written%20by%20a%20prominent%20employee%20of%20the%20East%20India%20Company%2C%20Mountstuart%20Elphinstone%2C%20who%20retired%20as%20governor%20of%20Bombay%20presidency%20in%201827.%20Elphinstone%E2%80%99s%3Cem%3E%20History%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20published%20in%20two%20volumes%20in%201841.%20The%20title%20was%20modified%20when%20the%20third%20edition%20was%20published%20in%201849%3A%20%3Cem%3EThe%20History%20of%20India%3A%20The%20Hindu%20and%20Mahometan%20Periods%3C%2Fem%3E.%20These%20labels%20had%20come%20to%20stay.%20A%20great%20deal%20of%20scholarly%20effort%20was%20required%20to%20undo%20such%20a%20chronological%20division.%20Historical%20works%20published%20since%20the%201950s%20have%20to%20a%20large%20extent%20undermined%20this%20understanding%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20past%2C%20at%20least%20in%20academic%20writings.%20Simultaneously%20it%20continues%20to%20be%20central%20to%20communal%20assertions%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20going%20into%20the%20complex%20historical%20problem%20of%20how%20%E2%80%98foreignness%E2%80%99%20is%20to%20be%20defined%20in%20the%20context%20of%20pre-modern%20societies%2C%20before%20the%20emergence%20of%20modern%20nation-states%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20draw%20attention%20to%20the%20specific%20character%20of%20colonialism%20as%20a%20system%20of%20exploitation%2C%20of%20extraction%20of%20wealth%20which%20then%20is%20transferred%20to%20the%20metropole.%20The%20ruling%20elites%20of%20the%20metropole%2C%20in%20this%20case%20Britain%2C%20were%20the%20main%20beneficiaries%20of%20this%20system%20using%20it%20to%20augment%20their%20own%20wealth%20manifold.%20The%20Industrial%20Revolution%20in%20England%2C%20which%20gathered%20momentum%20in%20the%20latter%20half%20of%20the%20eighteenth%20century%2C%20could%20not%20have%20been%20sustained%20without%20the%20resources%20pumped%20out%20of%20Bengal%20and%20Bihar%20especially%20after%20the%20battles%20of%20Plassey%20(1757)%20and%20of%20Baksar%20(1764)%2C%20and%20transferred%20in%20various%20ways%20to%20the%20metropole.%20While%20Britain%20grew%20rich%20and%20became%20the%20foremost%20capitalist%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20India%20became%20poorer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pioneers%20of%20economic%20nationalism%2C%20Dadabhai%20Naoroji%20and%20R.C.%20Dutt%2C%20assiduously%20studied%20a%20mass%20of%20official%20statistics%20and%20were%20able%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20British%20rule%20had%20systematically%20impoverished%20the%20Indian%20people%20through%20a%20mechanism%20whereby%20their%20resources%20were%20drained%20away%20continuously.%20Salaries%20and%20pensions%20of%20the%20colonial%20establishment%2C%20in%20India%20as%20well%20as%20in%20Britain%2C%20were%20paid%20out%20of%20Indian%20revenues.%20The%20triangular%20trade%20which%20involved%20the%20purchase%20of%20Chinese%20tea%20for%20the%20European%20market%20with%20profits%20earned%20from%20smuggling%20opium%20produced%20in%20India%20into%20China%20(opium%20was%20a%20monopoly%20of%20the%20colonial%20state)%2C%20i.e.%2C%20opium%20to%20China%2C%20and%20tea%20to%20England.%20This%20was%20an%20important%20channel%20for%20transmitting%20private%20earnings%20from%20India%20to%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20part%20of%20the%20mechanism%20which%20was%20not%20easily%20discernible%20was%20the%20one%20whereby%20India%20exported%20goods%20to%20Britain%20without%20getting%20anything%20in%20return.%20Whereas%20throughout%20the%2019th%20century%20and%20early%2020th%20century%20India%20had%20a%20favourable%20balance%20of%20trade%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20Britain%2C%20it%20had%20no%20real%20earnings%20from%20this%20trade.%20British%20importers%20made%20payments%20in%20pounds%20sterling%20to%20the%20secretary%20of%20state%E2%80%99s%20treasury%20in%20London%2C%20receiving%20Council%20Bills%20against%20these%20payments.%20These%20could%20be%20encashed%20by%20exporters%20in%20India%20in%20rupees%2C%20and%20were%20paid%20out%20of%20Indian%20revenues.%20The%20specificity%20of%20colonial%20rule%20lay%20in%20the%20operation%20of%20this%20mechanism%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20other%20means%20through%20which%20the%20British%20ruling%20elite%20extracted%20wealth%20from%20India%20over%20nearly%20two%20centuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20made%20possible%20by%20the%20political%20control%20which%20was%20exercised%20by%20the%20colonial%20state.%20It%20unleashed%20its%20full%20military%20might%20to%20brutally%20suppress%20the%20revolt%20of%201857%2C%20amounting%20to%20a%20reconquest%20of%20the%20empire.%20The%20drain%20of%20wealth%20could%20then%20continue%20for%20another%2090%20years.%20To%20club%20the%20centuries%20which%20preceded%20British%20rule%20with%20the%20era%20of%20colonialism%20is%20to%20trivialise%20colonial%20exploitation%2C%20the%20long%20history%20of%20resistance%20to%20it%20and%20the%20glorious%20legacy%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmar%20Farooqui%20taught%20history%20at%20Delhi%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689769855000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19152924%2Fdelhi-durbar-1911-16609.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fclaiming-india-saw-1000-years-of-foreign-rule-trivialises-british-colonial-exploitation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20British%20were%20responsible%20for%20dividing%20the%20history%20of%20pre-colonial%20India%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20period'%20and%20a%20%E2%80%98Muslim%20period%E2%80%99.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20continues%20to%20use%20that%20now-undermined%20distinction.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fclaiming-india-saw-1000-years-of-foreign-rule-trivialises-british-colonial-exploitation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HDFC%20Bank%20can%20now%20take%20mega%20exposures%20to%20infra%20projects%3A%20CEO%20Jagdishan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689769685000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-03%2F01%2Ffull%2F1677681429-7762.JPG%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmerger-helps-take-large-exposure-in-infra-projects-hdfc-bank-ceo-jagdishan-123071900757_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Post%20merger%2C%20Jagdishan%20aims%20to%20double%20business%20every%204%20years%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmerger-helps-take-large-exposure-in-infra-projects-hdfc-bank-ceo-jagdishan-123071900757_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmerger-helps-take-large-exposure-in-infra-projects-hdfc-bank-ceo-jagdishan-1230719007