Cp%3EThe%20charges%20included%20not%20only%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cspreading%20false%20news%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20also%20%E2%80%9Charming%20national%20security%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cincitement%20to%20overthrow%20the%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVerdict%20can%C2%A0strain%20relations%20with%20Italy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmnesty%20International%E2%80%99s%20Italian%20branch%20called%20the%20ruling%20%E2%80%9Ca%20scandalous%20verdict.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0According%20to%20rights%20defenders%2C%C2%A0Zaki%20was%20beaten%20and%20tortured%20with%20electricity%20during%20his%20detention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThousands%20signed%20petitions%20in%20Italy%20calling%20for%20Zaki%E2%80%99s%20release%2C%20and%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20Senate%20voted%20to%20grant%20him%20Italian%20citizenship%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelations%20between%20Cairo%20and%20Rome%20had%20previously%20been%20strained%20by%20the%202016%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fegyptians-stand-trial-over-murder-of-italian-student-in-cairo%2Fa-59498732%5C%22%3Ekilling%20of%20Italian%20doctoral%20student%20Giulio%20Regeni%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20Egypt%2C%20sparking%20concerns%20about%20academic%20freedom%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEgypt%20ranks%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20Academic%20Freedom%20Index%2C%20with%20researchers%20frequently%20detained%20and%20harassed%20for%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Edh%2Fwmr%20(AFP%2C%20Reuters)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fegypt-researcher-patrick-zaki-sentenced-to-3-years-in-jail%2Fa-66275354%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689764081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19160856%2Fpatrick-zaki.jpg%22%2C%22ori