will-severely-restrict-scope-of-rti-act-activists-write-to-mps%5C%22%3Ewas%20criticised%3C%2Fa%3E%20both%20by%20transparency%20activists%20and%20those%20campaigning%20for%20the%20right%20to%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20version%20of%20the%20Bill%20that%20finally%20received%20the%20nod%20of%20the%20cabinet%20is%20not%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20data%20protection%20law%20does%20not%20suffer%20from%20the%20pitfalls%20that%20the%20previous%20draft%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20law%20must%20not%20dilute%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act%2C%20which%20has%20empowered%20millions%20of%20Indian%20citizens%20since%20its%20enactment%20in%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20effectively%20hold%20their%20governments%20accountable%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20people%20need%20access%20to%20information%2C%20including%20various%20categories%20of%20personal%20data.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20held%20that%20citizens%20have%20a%20right%20to%20know%20the%20names%20of%20wilful%20defaulters%20and%20details%20of%20non-performing%20assets%20(NPAs)%20of%20public%20sector%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDemocracies%20routinely%20ensure%20public%20disclosure%20of%20voters%E2%80%99%20lists%20with%20names%2C%20addresses%2C%20and%20other%20personal%20data%20to%20enable%20public%20scrutiny%20and%20prevent%20electoral%20fraud.%20Experience%20of%20the%20use%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20in%20India%20has%20shown%20that%20if%20people%2C%20especially%20the%20poor%20and%20marginalised%2C%20are%20to%20have%20any%20hope%20of%20obtaining%20the%20benefits%20of%20government%20schemes%20and%20welfare%20programmes%2C%20they%20must%20have%20access%20to%20relevant%2C%20granular%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20Public%20Distribution%20System%20(PDS)%20Control%20Order%20recognises%20the%20need%20for%20putting%20the%20details%20of%20ration%20card%20holders%20and%20records%20of%20ration%20shops%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20to%20enable%20public%20scrutiny%20and%20social%20audits%20of%20the%20PDS.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20such%20publicly%20accessible%20personal%20data%2C%20it%20is%20impossible%20for%20intended%20beneficiaries%20to%20access%20their%20rightful%20entitlement%20of%20foodgrains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20protect%20peoples%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20the%20RTI%20Act%20includes%20an%20exemption%20clause%20under%20section%208(1)(j).%20In%20order%20to%20invoke%20this%20section%20to%20deny%20personal%20information%2C%20at%20least%20one%20of%20the%20following%20grounds%20has%20to%20be%20proven%3A%20the%20information%20sought%20has%20no%20relationship%20to%20any%20public%20activity%20or%20has%20no%20relationship%20to%20any%20public%20interest%3B%20or%20the%20information%20sought%20is%20such%20that%20it%20would%20cause%20unwarranted%20invasion%20of%20privacy%20and%20the%20information%20officer%20is%20satisfied%20that%20there%20is%20no%20larger%20public%20interest%20that%20justifies%20disclosure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20of%202022%20includes%20a%20provision%20to%20amend%20section%208(1)(j)%20to%20expand%20its%20purview%20and%20exempt%20all%20personal%20information%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act!%20This%20would%20be%20a%20huge%20blow%20to%20the%20transparency%20regime%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20must%20be%20harmonised%20with%20the%20provisions%20and%20objectives%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act.%20This%20would%20be%20in%20line%20with%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Justice%20A.P.%20Shah%20report%20on%20privacy%20that%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Privacy%20Act%20should%20clarify%20that%20publication%20of%20personal%20data%20for%20public%20interest%E2%80%A6%20and%20disclosure%20of%20information%20as%20required%20by%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20should%20not%20constitute%20an%20infringement%20of%20privacy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeither%20the%20recognition%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Privacy%2C%20nor%20the%20enactment%20of%20a%20data%20protection%20law%2C%20requires%20any%20amendment%20to%20the%20existing%20RTI%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Factivists-information-commissioners-fear-data-protection-bill-will-crush-rti-act-provisions%5C%22%3EActivists%2C%20Information%20Commissioners%20Fear%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Will%20Crush%20RTI%20Act%20Provisions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20given%20that%20the%20government%20is%20the%20biggest%20data%20repository%2C%20the%20law%20must%20not%20give%20wide%20discretionary%20powers%20to%20the%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20DPDP%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20however%2C%20empowers%20the%20government%20to%20draft%20rules%20and%20notifications%20on%20a%20vast%20range%20of%20issues.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20exempt%20any%20government%20or%20even%20private%20sector%20entity%20from%20the%20application%20of%20provisions%20of%20the%20law%20by%20merely%20issuing%20a%20notification%2C%20potentially%20resulting%20in%20immense%20violations%20of%20citizens%E2%80%99%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20small%20NGOs%2C%20research%20organisations%2C%20associations%20of%20persons%2C%20and%20opposition%20parties%20that%20the%20government%20chooses%20not%20to%20include%20in%20the%20notification%20would%20have%20to%20set%20up%20systems%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20stringent%20obligations%20of%20a%20data%20fiduciary%20as%20described%20in%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20that%20the%20oversight%20body%20set%20up%20under%20the%20legislation%20is%20adequately%20independent%20to%20act%20on%20violations%20of%20the%20law%20by%20government%20entities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20Bill%20does%20not%20ensure%20autonomy%20of%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20%E2%80%93%20the%20institution%20responsible%20for%20the%20enforcement%20of%20provisions%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwill-the-upcoming-personal-data-protection-law-live-up-to-years-of-expectations%5C%22%3Eis%20empowered%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20determine%20the%20strength%20and%20composition%20of%20the%20Board%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20process%20of%20selection%20and%20removal%20of%20its%20chairperson%20and%20other%20members.%20Further%2C%20the%20chief%20executive%20responsible%20for%20managing%20the%20Board%20is%20to%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20government%2C%20giving%20it%20direct%20control%20over%20the%20institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20is%20also%20empowered%20to%20assign%20the%20Board%20any%20functions%20%E2%80%9Cunder%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20Act%20or%20under%20any%20other%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20creation%20of%20a%20totally%20government-controlled%20Data%20Protection%20Board%2C%20vested%20with%20powers%20of%20a%20civil%20court%20and%20empowered%20to%20impose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fgovt-proposes-penalty-of-up-to-rs-500-crore-for-data-breach-under-data-protection-bill%2Farticleshow%2F95600084.cms%5C%22%3Efines%20of%20up%20Rs%20500%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20bound%20to%20raise%20serious%20apprehensions%20of%20it%20becoming%20another%20caged%20parrot%2C%20open%20to%20misuse%20by%20the%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFourth%2C%20the%20law%20must%20provide%20an%20accessible%2C%20people-friendly%20framework%20of%20grievance%20redress%20for%20affected%20persons%20to%20approach%20the%20oversight%20body.%20The%202022%20Bill%20stipulates%20that%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20shall%20be%20%E2%80%98digital%20by%20design%2C%E2%80%99%20including%20receipt%20and%20disposal%20of%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20latest%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey-5%2C%20only%20one%20in%20three%20women%20in%20India%20(33%25)%20ever%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fnfhs-data-shows-urban-rural-gender-gaps-in-internet-use-7103710%2F%5C%22%3Eused%20the%20internet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20DPDP%20Bill%2C%20therefore%2C%20effectively%20fails%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20the%20country%20who%20do%20not%20have%20meaningful%20access%20to%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20data%20breach%2C%20the%20victim%20must%20be%20able%20to%20seek%20monetary%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20DPDP%20Bill%20has%20no%20provision%20for%20compensation%20of%20any%20form.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Bill%20defines%20duties%20of%20a%20data%20principal%20(those%20whose%20personal%20data%20is%20collected)%20and%20provides%20for%20penalty%20imposition%20on%20them%20for%20registering%20frivolous%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20authors%20are%20associated%20with%20the%20National%20Campaign%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%20Information%20and%20Satark%20Nagrik%20Sangathan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689762651000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F01151611%2Fdata-protection.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchanges-to-rti-act-rs-500-crore-fine-five-pitfalls-to-watch-out-for-in-the-data-protection-law%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20version%20of%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20that%20received%20the%20cabinet%20nod%20is%20not%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20law%20does%20not%20suffer%20from%20the%20pitfalls%20that%20the%20previous%20draft%20had.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchanges-to-rti-act-rs-500-crore-fine-five-pitfalls-to-watch-out-for-in-the-data-protection-law%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%