ion%20of%20providing%20relief%20to%20the%20surviving%20families%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20arise%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20absurd%20and%20tragic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20images%20of%20the%20workers%E2%80%99%20chapattis%2C%20clothes%20and%20other%20personal%20items%C2%A0strewn%20on%20the%20railway%20tracks%20became%20the%20only%20%E2%80%98record%E2%80%99%20that%20those%2016%20deaths%20did%20occur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F09142110%2F2020_5img08_May_2020_PTI08-05-2020_000032B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F09142110%2F2020_5img08_May_2020_PTI08-05-2020_000032B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F09142110%2F2020_5img08_May_2020_PTI08-05-2020_000032B-300x191.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F09142110%2F2020_5img08_May_2020_PTI08-05-2020_000032B-1024x652.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-453595%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22764%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPolice%20at%20the%20site%20where%20migrant%20labourers%20making%20there%20way%20home%20during%20the%20lockdown%20were%20mowed%20down%20by%20a%20train.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFast%20forward%20to%20July%202023%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Thousands%20of%20migrant%20workers%20living%20in%20shanty%20colonies%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Yamuna%20in%20Delhi%20are%20homeless.%20Flowing%20way%20above%20its%20%E2%80%98danger%20mark%E2%80%99%20for%20days%2C%20the%20Yamuna%20has%20again%20submerged%20their%20homes.%20Thanks%20to%20climate%20change%2C%20this%20monsoon%20deluge%20is%20now%20more%20destructive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%201978%2C%20the%20Yamuna%20has%20crossed%20the%20207%20metre%20mark%20three%20times%2C%20all%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years%20%E2%80%93%202013%2C%202019%20and%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20time%2C%20the%20worst%20hit%20are%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20migrant%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FNZuAJSal-Mg%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Truth%20of%20Delhi's%20Relief%20Camps%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20Are%20Surviving%20Only%20on%20Rice%26quot%3B%20%7C%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20%7C%20Ground%20Report%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20crores%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20vulnerable%2C%20most%20marginalised%2C%20and%20most%20%E2%80%98invisible%E2%80%99%20socio-economic%20group%20%E2%80%93%20internal%20migrant%20workers%20%E2%80%93%20suffer%20the%20most%20due%20to%20natural%20and%20man-made%20disasters.%20They%20are%20ignored%20by%20their%20home%20states%20and%20their%20host%20states.%20Most%20of%20them%20are%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20minority%20communities%2C%20or%20India%E2%80%99s%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Tribes.%20Eight%20of%20the%20men%20run%20over%20by%20the%20goods%20train%20in%202020%20were%20Gond%20Adivasis.%20Unfortunately%2C%20as%20most%20migrant%20workers%20can%E2%80%99t%20even%20exercise%20their%20vote%2C%20they%20also%20lack%20that%20last%20bit%20of%20clout%20over%20the%20political%20class%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3Esarkari%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ebabu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20other%20Indians%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20be%20clear%2C%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20a%20vast%20number%20of%20fellow%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%202014%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmpra.ub.uni-muenchen.de%2F19193%2F1%2FMPRA_paper_19193.pdf%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20India%20has%20a%20100%20million%20temporary%20internal%20migrant%20workers%2C%20with%20roughly%2050%25%20%E2%80%98intra-state%E2%80%99%20and%2050%25%20%E2%80%98inter-state%E2%80%99%20migrant%20workers.%20As%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20has%20risen%20by%20almost%2010%25%20since%202014%2C%20the%20number%20today%20should%20be%20around%20110%20million.%20The%20study%20also%20estimated%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20internal%20migrant%20workers%20contributed%2010%25%20to%20the%20national%20GDP.%20An%20irony%2C%20because%20they%20get%20very%20little%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Maharashtra%2C%20the%20Delhi%20National%20Capital%20Region%20(NCR)%20hosts%20India%E2%80%99s%20second%20highest%20population%20of%20migrant%20workers%20%E2%80%93%20factory%20hands%2C%20loaders%2C%20rickshaw%20pullers%2C%20street%20vendors%2C%20masons%2C%20security%20guards%2C%20cleaners%2C%20gig%20workers%2C%20domestic%20helps%20%E2%80%93%20all%20barely%20scraping%20a%20living.%20Work%20in%20the%20unorganised%20and%20informal%20sector%20means%20zero%20job%20security.%20Migrant%20workers%20often%20work%20for%20less%20than%20minimum%20wages%2C%20work%20long%20hours%2C%20and%20work%20in%20unsafe%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20employers%2C%20they%20are%20also%20exploited%20by%20middlemen%20and%20labour%20contractors%20on%20whom%20they%20rely%20to%20find%20work.%20With%20very%20little%20to%20survive%20on%2C%20the%20Yamuna%E2%80%99s%20floodplains%20offer%20the%20cheapest%20real%20estate%20to%20them.%20And%20so%2C%20most%20residents%20in%20the%20shanty%20colonies%20on%20the%20Yamuna%20floodplains%2C%20and%20on%20the%20margins%20of%20the%20scores%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Enallahs%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20that%20wind%20towards%20the%20Yamuna%2C%20are%20migrant%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELiving%20conditions%20here%20are%20highly%20inadequate%20%E2%80%93%20these%20shanty%20colonies%20are%20over-crowded%2C%20with%20little%20access%20to%20sanitation%2C%20water%2C%20electricity.%20Despite%20being%20far%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20disease%20in%20such%20unhygienic%20conditions%2C%20migrant%20workers%20have%20poor%20access%20to%20healthcare%20facilities.%20They%20also%20know%20the%20Yamuna%20floods%20almost%20every%20monsoon%2C%20but%20are%20forced%20to%20take%20their%20chances.%20And%20almost%20every%20year%2C%20they%20endure%20a%20cycle%20of%20flooding%2C%20packing%20their%20belongings%20and%20slumming%20it%20on%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20pavements%20for%20weeks%2C%20and%20then%20having%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20rebuild%20their%20shanties%20on%20the%20same%20floodplain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13143213%2Fsignal-2023-07-13-141935_002.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13143213%2Fsignal-2023-07-13-141935_002.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13143213%2Fsignal-2023-07-13-141935_002-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13143213%2Fsignal-2023-07-13-141935_002-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-662994%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Yamuna%20flooding.%20Photo%3A%20Shekhar%20Tiwari%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20migrant%20workers%C2%A0went%20through%C2%A0during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20should%20have%20been%20a%20tipping%20point%2C%20pushing%20state%20governments%20and%20the%20central%20government%20to%20finally%20think%20of%20ways%20to%20improve%20their%C2%A0lives%2C%20but%20that%20has%20simply%20not%20happened.%C2%A0Stranded%20Workers%20Action%20Network%20(SWAN)%2C%20a%20volunteer%20group%20that%20provided%20relief%20to%20migrant%20workers%C2%A0during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20also%20compiled%20their%20testimonies.%20Their%20report%20about%20what%20migrant%20workers%20faced%20during%20the%20pandemic%E2%80%99s%20deadly%20second%20wave%20in%20April%20and%20May%202021%2C%20reveals%20just%20how%20vulnerable%20migrant%20workers%20can%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20report%20says%20that%2082%25%20of%20the%20workers%20had%20just%20two%20days%20of%20rations%20left%20at%20the%20time%20that%20SWAN%20reached%20them.%20As%20many%20as%2076%25%20of%20them%20had%20just%20Rs%20200%20left%20with%20them%2C%2092%25%20had%20not%20received%20any%20money%20from%20their%20employer%20after%20work%20stopped%20and%2056%25%20of%20the%20workers%20had%20been%20without%20work%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20evidence%20that%20we%20remain%20unmoved%20despite%20being%20aware%20of%20the%20hardships%20faced%20by%20migrant%20workers%2C%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnikhil-dey-mgnrega-budget-cut-2023%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThis%2520time%252C%2520the%2520allocation%2520has%2Clow%2520of%2520Rs%252060%252C000%2520crore.%26amp%3Btext%3DTalking%2520to%2520The%2520Wire%252C%2520Dey%2Ccrore%2520was%2520needed%2520for%2520MGNREGA.%5C%22%3Ecut%20in%20MGNREGA%20spend%20in%20the%202023-24%20Union%20Budget%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20fact%20is%20that%20the%20needs%20of%20migrant%20workers%20are%20known.%20Almost%20all%20of%20them%20work%20without%20a%20contract%2C%20which%20makes%20them%20vulnerable.%20Most%20migrant%20workers%C2%A0are%20not%20unionised%2C%20which%20makes%20them%C2%A0further%C2%A0vulnerable.%C2%A0They%20also%20need%20an%20urban%20employment%20guarantee%20system%20and%20a%20system%20of%20wage%20support%20or%20social%20security%20in%20the%20event%20of%20job%20loss.%20A%20strong%20grievance%20redressal%20system%20that%20deters%20employers%20is%20also%20needed.%20So%2C%20why%20have%20these%20needs%20not%20been%20addressed%20over%20the%20years%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20reason%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20political%20or%20electoral%20clout.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%2060%25%20of%20migrant%20workers%20don%E2%80%99t%20return%20home%20and%20vote%20in%20national%20elections%2C%20often%20skipping%20state%20elections%20too.%20But%20they%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20power%20of%20their%20vote%2C%20many%20of%20them%20choosing%20to%20return%20to%20vote%20for%20local%20elections.%20A%202012%20study%20showed%20that%20a%20robust%2078%25%20of%20migrant%20voters%20even%20had%20voter%20i-cards%20for%20their%20home%20constituency.%20Their%20absence%20is%20even%20reflected%20in%20the%20voter%20turnout%20figures%20for%20UP%20and%20Bihar%2C%20the%20most%20prolific%20migrant%20worker%20%E2%80%98sender%E2%80%99%20states.%20In%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20Bihar%20and%20UP%20had%20among%20the%20lowest%20voter%20turnouts%20at%2057%25%20and%2059%25%20respectively%2C%20below%20the%20national%20average%20of%2067.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbengal-panchayat-election-tea-garden%5C%22%3EWhy%20There%E2%80%99s%20No%20One%20Left%20to%20Vote%20in%20North%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20Tea%20Gardens%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20migrant%20workers%20prefer%20to%20retain%20their%20home%20state%20vote%2C%20those%20who%20want%20to%20vote%20from%20their%20%E2%80%98host%E2%80%99%20state%2C%20often%20run%20into%20red%20tape%2C%20unable%20to%20provide%20proof%20of%20residence.%C2%A0Many%20migrant%20workers%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20rickshaw%20pullers%20simply%20live%20on%20and%20around%20their%20rickshaws.%20While%20construction%20workers%20often%20shift%20from%20one%20work%20site%20to%20another.%C2%A0India%E2%80%99s%C2%A0hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20migrant%20workers%C2%A0are%C2%A0%E2%80%98invisible%E2%80%99%20politically.%20Their%20inability%20to%20vote%20keeps%20them%20from%20forming%20an%C2%A0electoral%20block%2C%20whose%20interests%20the%20politicians%20would%20then%20be%20pressured%20to%20serve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F26194618%2F2020_3img26_Mar_2020_PTI26-03-2020_000214B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F26194618%2F2020_3img26_Mar_2020_PTI26-03-2020_000214B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F26194618%2F2020_3img26_Mar_2020_PTI26-03-2020_000214B-300x192.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F26194618%2F2020_3img26_Mar_2020_PTI26-03-2020_000214B-1024x656.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-444044%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22769%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20group%20of%20migrant%20labourers%20walk%20to%20their%20villages%20amid%20a%20national%20lockdown%2C%20on%20the%20NH24%20near%20the%20Delhi-UP%20border%2C%20March%2026%2C%202020.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%2FRavi%20Choudhary%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20already%20has%20solutions%20for%20these%20hurdles%2C%20but%20has%20just%20not%20applied%20them%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20migrant%20workers.%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98netas%E2%80%99%20too%2C%20are%20guilty%20of%20not%20pressing%20hard%20enough.%20After%20all%2C%20providing%20for%20the%20migrant%20workers%20as%20%E2%80%98host%E2%80%99%20states%20or%20cities%2C%20after%20they%20acquired%20political%20heft%2C%20would%20be%20an%20additional%20fiscal%20challenge%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20additional%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20homeless%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20provided%20for%20verification%20via%20local%20block%20officers.%20A%20similar%20solution%20could%20be%20provided%20to%20migrant%20workers%20as%20well.%20And%20for%20migrant%20workers%C2%A0preferring%20to%20retain%20their%20home%20state%20voter%20status%2C%20the%20EC%20could%20give%20them%20access%20to%20the%20already%20existing%20system%20of%20electronically-transmitted%20postal%20ballot%20(ETPB).%20In%202019%2C%20the%20ETPB%20option%20was%20provided%20to%2018%20lakh%20defence%20personnel%20across%20India.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20proposal%20to%20give%20such%20a%20%E2%80%98remote%20voting%E2%80%99%20option%20to%20NRIs%20across%20the%20world%20as%20well.%20Why%20not%20provide%20the%20same%20to%20migrant%20workers%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20measures%20will%20ensure%20that%20migrant%20workers%20are%20heard%20by%20politicians%20and%20government%20servants%20in%20the%20cities%20that%20they%20contribute%20so%20much%20to.%20Even%20the%20option%20of%20voting%20remotely%20in%20their%20home%20state%2C%20will%20force%20politicians%20to%20push%20for%20their%20demands%20in%20their%20host%C2%A0states%20and%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20when%C2%A0India%E2%80%99s%20migrant%20workers%C2%A0will%20have%20some%20chance%20of%20being%C2%A0more%20%E2%80%98visible%E2%80%99%2C%20more%20%E2%80%98heard%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERohit%20Khanna%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20video%20storyteller.%20He%20has%20been%20Managing%20Editor%20at%20The%20Quint%2C%20and%20is%20a%20two-time%20Ramnath%20Goenka%20award%20winner.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689760915000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19152537%2FUntitled-design-27.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Finvisible-migrant-worker-flood-covid%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20key%20reason%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20political%20or%20electoral%20clout.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Finvisible-migrant-worker-flood-covid%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2