%20it%20is%20overturned%20or%20modified%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcourt-order-on-disney-s-in-app-payment-in-india-temporary-google-123071900438_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcourt-order-on-disney-s-in-app-payment-in-india-temporary-google-123071900438_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcourt-order-on-disney-s-in-app-payment-in-india-temporary-google-123071900438_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Air%20Pollution%20Reduces%20India%E2%80%99s%20y-o-y%20GDP%20Growth%20by%200.56%20Percentage%20Points%3A%20World%20Bank%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F27174427%2FDelhi-Pollution-PTI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERising%20air%20pollution%20reduces%20India%E2%80%99s%20year-on-year%20gross%20domestic%20product%20(GDP)%20growth%20by%200.56%20percentage%20points%2C%20a%20World%20Bank%20report%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETitled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocuments1.worldbank.org%2Fcurated%2Fen%2F099710506302335471%2Fpdf%2FIDU0536186520dc340403409fb001cfc637a9368.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAir%20Pollution%20Reduces%20Economic%20Activity%3A%20Evidence%20from%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20policy%20research%20working%20paper%20explores%20how%20exposure%20to%20fine%20particulate%20matter%20(PM2.5)%20has%20affected%20economic%20growth%20in%20districts%20across%20the%20country.%20It%20used%20changes%20in%20the%20annual%20GDP%20of%20districts%20to%20investigate%20the%20impact%20of%20changes%20in%20the%20level%20of%20ambient%20PM2.5%20on%20the%20district-level%20GDP%20in%20the%201998-2020%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20is%20authored%20by%20A.%20Patrick%20Behrer%2C%20Rishabh%20Choudhary%20and%20Dhruv%20Sharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20collated%20data%20for%20approximately%20550%20districts%2C%20covering%20around%2025%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20(UTs)%2C%20with%20each%20having%2C%20on%20average%2C%2015%20observations.%20These%20states%20and%20UTs%20contribute%2090%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20real%20GDP%2C%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CExposure%20to%20PM2.5%20in%20India%20has%20increased%20significantly%20over%20time%20as%20well.%20During%20our%20sample%20period%2C%20average%20exposures%20have%20increased%20by%20more%20than%2050%25%2C%20from%20approximately%2035%C2%B5g%2Fm3%20to%20more%20than%2055%C2%B5g%2Fm3.%20The%20impact%20of%20COVID-19%20lockdowns%20on%20pollution%20is%20visible%20as%20a%20notable%20decline%20in%20average%20pollution%20levels%20at%20the%20end%20of%20our%20sample%20period%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19130333%2Fimage-1136.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221163%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19130333%2Fimage-1136.png%201163w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19130333%2Fimage-1136-300x185.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19130333%2Fimage-1136-1024x630.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663923%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22716%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20World%20Bank%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98Air%20Pollution%20Reduces%20Economic%20Activity%3A%20Evidence%20from%20India%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20Weighted%20average%20PM2.5%20(%CE%BCg%2Fm3)%20with%20averages%20calculated%20across%20districts%20in%20each%20fiscal%20year.%20District%20level%20averages%20are%20calculated%20by%20averaging%20across%20grid-points%20within%20the%20district%20and%20weighting%20each%20grid-point%20by%20the%20population%20of%20the%20surrounding%20area.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20levels%20of%20exposure%20to%20PM2.5%20in%20India%20exceed%2050%C2%B5g%2Fm3%2C%20and%20in%20some%20districts%2C%20it%20also%20exceeds%20100%C2%B5g%2Fm3.%20That%20is%20roughly%2020%20times%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20(WHO)%20recommended%20levels%20and%20more%20than%20double%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20standards.%20Peak%20exposure%20in%20Delhi%20can%20exceed%20500%C2%B5g%2Fm3%2C%20the%20report%20underlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20quotes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw27398%5C%22%3Eanother%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%20to%20say%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctrue%20growth%20rates%20in%20India%20have%20been%20an%20average%20of%2050%20basis%20points%20lower%20than%20reported%20rates%20since%202005%20due%20to%20the%20negative%20consequences%20of%20pollution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20adverse%20impact%20of%20air%20pollution%20on%20economic%20growth%20stems%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20reduces%20worker%20productivity%20on%20the%20job%2C%20increases%20worker%20absenteeism%20due%20to%20illness%2C%20and%20directly%20harms%20agricultural%20productivity%2C%20the%20report%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20long-run%2C%20reductions%20in%20human%20capital%20formation%20and%20migration%20away%20from%20the%20most%20economically%20productive%20areas%20due%20to%20pollution%20exposure%20loom%20large%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20adds%2C%20emphasising%20that%20air%20pollution%20has%20a%20variety%20of%20negative%20impacts%20on%20workers%20and%20economic%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findian-economy-inflation-adani-press-freedom-politics%5C%22%3EFive%20Issues%20That%20Are%20Hurting%20the%20Indian%20Economy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20notes%20that%20reducing%20air%20pollution%20also%20has%20significant%20costs%20and%20may%20require%20structural%20changes%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy.%20%E2%80%9CSuch%20structural%20changes%20are%20likely%20to%20have%20direct%20impacts%20on%20growth%20rates%20that%20may%20be%20larger%2C%20and%20differently%20signed%2C%20than%20the%20impacts%20of%20reducing%20air%20pollution.%20Despite%20this%2C%20there%20are%20likely%20significant%20long-term%20benefits%20from%20reducing%20air%20pollution%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20help%20of%20the%20two%20graphs%20below%2C%20the%20report%20estimates%20that%20the%20Indian%20GDP%20would%20have%20been%204.51%25%20higher%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20period%20if%20pollution%20had%20grown%2050%25%20more%20slowly%20in%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19131234%2Fimage-1138.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22937%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19131234%2Fimage-1138.png%20937w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19131234%2Fimage-1138-300x204.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663926%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22637%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20World%20Bank%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98Air%20Pollution%20Reduces%20Economic%20Activity%3A%20Evidence%20from%20India%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(